VALUES
(40, 13, 33, 48, 5, 9, 9, 'leaven', 'Leaven''s Influence in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the transformative power of leaven. Matthew illustrates how the kingdom of heaven spreads like leaven, while Galatians warns that a small amount of leaven can affect the whole lump.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 33, 46, 5, 6, 7, NULL, 'Leaven as a Transformative Agent', 'Both passages emphasize the transformative nature of leaven, illustrating how a small amount can influence a larger whole. Matthew presents leaven as a metaphor for the kingdom of heaven, while 1 Corinthians warns against the corrupting influence of old leaven.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 33, 42, 13, 21, 21, NULL, 'Leaven as a Kingdom Metaphor', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of leaven hidden in meal, illustrating the transformative nature of the kingdom of heaven. The identical phrasing reinforces the idea of gradual influence and growth.', 'keyword', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 33, 50, 2, 13, 15, 'the whole was leavened', 'Transformation and Influence', 'This connection highlights the transformative nature of the kingdom of heaven and God''s work within believers. Both passages emphasize the idea of internal change leading to outward manifestation, as leaven permeates the meal and believers shine as lights.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 33, 20, 4, 18, 18, 'the whole was leavened', 'Growth and Illumination Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of gradual transformation. Both passages emphasize a process of growth, with leaven permeating the meal and the path of the just shining more and more.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 33, 1, 18, 6, 6, 'three measures of meal', 'Connection of Measures of Meal', 'Both passages emphasize ''three measures of meal,'' linking the act of preparation in Genesis with the transformative process in Matthew. This connection highlights the theme of growth and change associated with the kingdom of heaven.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 33, 18, 17, 9, 9, NULL, 'Strength in Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth and strength in righteousness. The leaven in Matthew symbolizes the transformative power of the kingdom, while Job emphasizes that the righteous will become stronger.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 34, 41, 4, 33, 34, 'without a parable spake he not unto them', 'Connection of Parables in Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize that Jesus spoke in parables to the multitude and only explained things to his disciples privately. This connection highlights the method of teaching used by Jesus in both accounts.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 34, 43, 16, 25, 25, 'spake he not unto them', 'Use of Parables and Proverbs', 'This connection highlights the method of teaching used by Jesus in both passages. Matthew emphasizes that Jesus spoke in parables, while John refers to his teachings as proverbs, indicating a similar style of conveying deeper truths.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 34, 40, 13, 13, 13, 'spake he not unto them', 'Connection of Parables in Matthew', 'Both passages emphasize the use of parables by Jesus. The first verse states that Jesus spoke to the multitude in parables, while the second explains the reason for this method, highlighting the audience''s inability to see and hear.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 35, 19, 78, 2, 2, 'I will open my mouth in parables', 'Connection of Parables in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the act of opening the mouth in parables to convey deeper truths. This connection highlights the continuity of using parables to reveal hidden meanings.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 35, 49, 3, 9, 9, 'kept secret from the foundation of the world', 'Mystery and Revelation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of revealing mysteries that were hidden. Both passages emphasize the unveiling of truths that have been kept secret since the foundation of the world.', 'theme', 0.5449999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 35, 45, 16, 25, 26, 'kept secret from the foundation of the world', 'Connection of Mysteries Revealed', 'Both passages emphasize things which have been kept secret since the world began. This connection highlights the revelation of divine truths through Jesus Christ and the prophets.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 35, 60, 1, 20, 21, 'from the foundation of the world', 'Connection of Foundations and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the concept of revelation ''from the foundation of the world.'' Both passages emphasize the unfolding of divine truths and purposes that were established before creation, linking the mystery of Christ''s foreordination with the revelation of parables.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 35, 46, 2, 7, 7, 'things which have been kept secret', 'Hidden Wisdom and Parables', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of hidden wisdom and mysteries that have been kept secret. Matthew speaks of uttering things kept secret from the foundation of the world, while 1 Corinthians refers to hidden wisdom ordained before the world.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 35, 43, 17, 24, 24, 'foundation of the world', 'Foundation of the World Connection', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''foundation of the world'' in both passages. Matthew speaks of secrets kept since the foundation, while John refers to love before the foundation, linking the divine purpose across time.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 35, 30, 3, 7, 7, 'things which have been kept secret', 'Revelation of Secrets', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation. Both passages emphasize the idea that God reveals secrets, with Matthew referencing the utterance of hidden truths and Amos stating that God reveals secrets to His prophets.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 36, 40, 13, 11, 11, NULL, 'Understanding the Mysteries of the Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the disciples'' desire to understand the parable, which relates to the idea of knowing the mysteries of the kingdom. Both passages emphasize the distinction between those who are given insight and those who are not.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 36, 43, 16, 17, 20, NULL, 'Disciples'' Inquiry and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the disciples'' desire for understanding in both passages. In Matthew, they seek clarification on a parable, while in John, they are confused about Jesus'' words, indicating a theme of seeking deeper insight.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 36, 40, 9, 28, 28, 'into the house', 'Jesus in the House', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus entering a house, which serves as a setting for significant interactions. In each instance, individuals approach Jesus for understanding or healing, highlighting his role as a teacher and healer.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 36, 41, 6, 45, 45, 'sent the multitude away', 'Sending Away the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize the act of sending away the people. In Matthew, Jesus sends the multitude away before explaining the parable, while in Mark, he sends the people away before directing his disciples.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 36, 41, 7, 17, 17, NULL, 'Disciples'' Inquiry in Private', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' questions to Jesus after he enters the house. This connection highlights their desire for deeper understanding of his teachings.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 37, 46, 3, 5, 7, 'soweth the good seed', 'Connection of Sowing and Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the roles of sowing and growth in ministry. Matthew identifies the sower as the Son of man, while 1 Corinthians discusses the planting and watering done by Paul and Apollos, highlighting that ultimately, God is responsible for the increase.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 37, 40, 13, 41, 41, 'the Son of man', 'Connection of the Son of Man', 'This connection highlights the role of the Son of man in both passages. In Matthew 13:37, he is identified as the sower of good seed, while in Matthew 13:41, he is depicted as the one who sends forth angels to gather out those who offend.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 37, 42, 10, 16, 16, 'He that soweth the good seed', 'Connection of Authority and Reception', 'This connection highlights the authority of the Son of Man as the one who sows good seed, paralleling the idea that hearing His messengers equates to hearing Him. Both passages emphasize the relationship between the sender and the sent, illustrating the importance of reception.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 37, 44, 1, 8, 8, 'soweth the good seed', 'Connection of Witness and Sowing', 'This connection highlights the role of the Son of man as the sower of good seed, which can be seen as the foundation for the witnesses empowered by the Holy Ghost. Both passages emphasize the spread of the message, from local to global.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 37, 40, 8, 20, 20, 'the Son of man', 'Connection of the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of the Son of Man. In Matthew 13:37, He is identified as the sower of good seed, while in Matthew 8:20, His lack of a place to rest highlights His humble existence.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 37, 43, 13, 20, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Sending and Receiving', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the sender and the sent. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing and receiving those who are sent by Jesus, linking the act of sowing good seed to the acceptance of His messengers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 37, 43, 20, 21, 21, 'the Son of man', 'Sending and Sowing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of sending. In Matthew, the Son of Man sows good seed, while in John, Jesus sends his disciples as he was sent. Both passages emphasize the continuation of Jesus'' mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 38, 43, 8, 44, 44, 'children of the wicked one', 'Children of the Wicked One', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the children of God and the children of the devil. Matthew identifies the children of the wicked one, while John explicitly states that those who lie are of their father, the devil.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
